<P>Cor charte appen|sum rosei vice cerne sigilli spret&acirc; morte, tui solus id egit amor.<NOTE PLACE="foot">Harl. 6848, In the attestation, <I>Mary</I> is spelled <I>Marie;</I> some of the words "Sealed and delivered," etc., are missing in the rotograph. CHS appears instead of IHS, and the remainder of the writing on the strap is lack|ing. <I>Chartae</I> appears instead of <I>Charte</I>.</NOTE></P>


