<L>ffor [no]<NOTE PLACE="foot">The letters in this word and in those bracketed in the two next lines are blurred.</NOTE> chalinge shuld be</L>
<L>ff[ul wor]&thorn;ely she kept me &amp; &thorn;e</L>
<L>[Tyl y] my tyme wolde y-se</L>
<L>ffourty wykes &amp; fourty dayes</L>
<L N="20">To fulfille &thorn;e ry&yogh;t lawes</L>
<L>&THORN;e maide was mylde trewe &amp; fre</L>
<L>She rekeued bo&thorn;e me and the</L>
<L>Me &thorn;i manhede and &thorn;y grace</L>
<L>&THORN;us com &thorn;e sesyng ferst a place</L>
<L N="25">Whan &thorn;is sesyng was y-do</L>
<L>Ful gret envye had &thorn;an &thorn;y fo</L>
<L>&THORN;o belsabub and sathanas</L>
