<L N="185">I made a sessynge whane I was bore</L>
<L>to mankende &thorn;at was for-lore</L>
<L>But wyth my charture here-in presente</L>
<L>I make to mannes Soule a feffemente</L>
<L>&THORN;at I haue grauntyd And I-&yogh;eue</L>
<L N="190">to mankend wyth me for to be</L>
<L>In my kyndome of heuene blysse<MILESTONE N="46a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>to haue and to holde wyth-owte mys</L>
<L>So in &thorn;is condycioun &thorn;at &thorn;ou be kende</L>
<L>And myne wondyrful dedys to haue in mende</L>
<L N="195">frely to haue and frely to holde</L>
<L>wyth all &thorn;e portenaunce with &thorn;e wolde</L>
<L>In my blysful Ioye euyr to dwelle</L>
<L>for &thorn;e rent &thorn;at I xal &thorn;e telle</L>
<L>Myn herytage &thorn;at is so fre</L>
<L N="200">for homage or for fewte</L>
<L>no more wyl I aske of the</L>
<L>But A iiij<SUP>e</SUP> leued gras rent to me</L>
<L>&THORN;e fyrst lefe is wery schryfte</L>
<L>&THORN;at other for &thorn;i synne thyn hert smerte</L>
<L N="205">the iij<SUP>de</SUP> Is I wyl do no more so</L>
<L>&THORN;e iiij<SUP>te</SUP> is the penaunce &thorn;ere-to</L>
<L>And haue thys leuys to-gedyr be set</L>
<L N="208">A trew loue me clepyth it
<PB REF="00000188.tif" N="64"></L>
<L N="209">of thys rent be &thorn;ou noughte be-hynde</L>
<L N="210">&THORN;e waye to heuene &thorn;ane may I fende</L>
<L>And if &thorn;ou thys rente trewly paye me</L>
<L N="212">My gret mercy I schewe the</L>
<L>for if &thorn;ou falle And gretly mistake</L>
<L>&yogh;et myn charture wyl I not for-sake</L>
<L N="215">&yogh;if &thorn;ou A-mende and mercy crawe</L>
<L>thyne herytage sothly &thorn;oue xalt haue</L>
<L>&THORN;e sealys &thorn;at it is a-selyd wyth</L>
<L>they werene I-made at a smyth</L>
<L>of gold ne syluere be they noughte</L>
<L>of stele And Irone they bene wroughte<MILESTONE N="46b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>for wyth a spere of stele myne hert &thorn;ei stonge</L>
<L>thorow my sydys and thorow myne lounge</L>
<L>vppone my syde they made a wounde</L>
<L>&THORN;at myn hert blood rane downe one grownde</L>
<L N="225">And with &thorn;e nayles they bored me</L>
<L>thorow feet &amp; hondys in-to &thorn;e tre</L>
<L>the selyng wexe was dere a-boughte</L>
<L>at myn hert rote it was soughte</L>
<L>al tempered wyth fyne vermeloun</L>
<L N="230">of myn reed blood &thorn;at ranne A-downe</L>
<L>v<SUP>e</SUP> seles bene sett vp-one</L>
<L N="232">fadyr and sone god &amp; mane
<PB REF="00000190.tif" N="66"></L>
<L N="233">&THORN;e fyrst &thorn;at is to be-leue most</L>
<L>&THORN;at I came of &thorn;e holy gost</L>
<L N="235">And &thorn;erre-for here may &thorn;ou see</L>
